<H3> <TI>   London Paper's Expose on Russia's `Secret Biological Weapons' </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    London Paper's Expose on Russia's `Secret Biological Weapons' </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Defense Ministry Denies Report </H4>

<F P=102> LD2803104894 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1038 GMT 28 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2803104894 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by ITAR-TASS correspondent Anatoliy Yurkin] </F>
  [Text] Moscow March 28 TASS -- Russia is neither developing 
nor producing biological weapons, a spokesman for the 
information and press department of the Defence Ministry told 
ITAR-TASS today, following reports in a number of foreign and 
Russian mass media organs, which maintain that Russia is 
allegedly continuing to implement a programme of creating 
biological weapons, specifically new "super-plague", to which 
the West has no antidote. 
  The foreign mass media quote reports of an anonymous 
intelligence source, which maintains that the programme is being 
implemented under the control of the Russian Defence Ministry. 
  In the opinion of experts from the Defence Ministry, it is 
rather astonishing that the forgery, circulated in the West in 
search of a sensation, was thoughtlessly repeated by some 
Russian mass media organs, which had ample opportunity to 
contact specialists and check the correctness of the reports. 

</TEXT>

