<H3> <TI>   Former ICBM's Used To Launch Satellites </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Former ICBM's Used To Launch Satellites </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PM1803112994 Moscow ROSSIYSKIYE VESTI in Russian 17 Mar 94 p 
11 </F>

<F P=103> PM1803112994 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ROSSIYSKIYE VESTI </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Unattributed report: "Satellite for Mail"] </F>
  [Text] Conversion is entering the life of the Russian 
Plesetsk cosmodrome increasingly widely. The Arkhangelsk Oblast 
newspaper VOLNA reports that last year regular launches of 
launch vehicles made on the basis of combat ICBM's. Thus with 
the aid of the new "Start-1" launch vehicle an experimental 
electronic mail satellite was put into orbit. 
  In all last year 36 space vehicles were launched from the 
world's northernmost cosmodrome, only eight of them in the 
interests of the Defense Ministry. This year's program includes 
the launch of the new "Koronas" geophysical satellite which will 
continue the study of the polar aurora in the upper strata of 
the atmosphere and will begin regular observations of the Sun. 
And the "Okean" satellite will search for shoals of fish and 
investigate the ice on Arctic shipping routes. 

</TEXT>

