<H3> <TI>   Recent Comments on Return of Nuclear Warheads to Russia </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Recent Comments on Return of Nuclear Warheads to Russia </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Further Zlenko Comment </H4>

<F P=102> LD2503093794 Moscow INTERFAX in English 0331 GMT 25 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2503093794 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow INTERFAX </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The Ukrainian Foreign Minister Anatoliy Zlenko told 
journalists on his return from a trip to Warsaw and Brussels 
that he shares the opinion of the Ukrainian defense minister 
about the possible adjustment of the timetable for the 
withdrawal of warheads from Ukraine. 
  In response to a question by the Interfax-Ukraine news 
agency, Zlenko said that "all signatories of the statement on 
nuclear disarmament of Ukraine should fulfil their obligations." 
  Earlier this week Ukrainian leaders stated that Ukraine may 
suspend the withdrawal of warheads unless Russia starts 
transportation of nuclear fuel for Ukrainian nuclear power 
stations. 
  "We are entitled to issue a statement and take corresponding 
measures in order to fulfil obligations assumed under the 
trilateral statement," Zlenko said. 
  Asked about the U.S. role in the fulfillment of obligations 
under the statement, Zlenko said: "We are talking about equal 
partnership. Each side should assume equal obligations." 

</TEXT>

