  [Text] Bonn (DPA) -- Foreign Minister Klaus Kinkel, of the 
Free Democratic Party of Germany, on Wednesday praised U.S. 
President Clinton's decision to extend the moratorium on nuclear 
tests by another year until September 1995 as exemplary for 
other nations. It will "significantly increase" the chances to 
achieve an unlimited test ban treaty in the Geneva moratorium 
talks. 

