  [Text] Must we once again fear the Russian military? 
  The generals in Moscow have developed a new chemical weapon. 
The project is considered to be a state secret (code: "A 
232"). A scientist who informed the west about it was arrested 
for betraying state secrets. 
  The nerve poison (called "Novikhok") reportedly works even 
faster and more strongly than all chemical combat agents known 
so far. Bonn is alarmed. Dieter Kastrup, state secretary in the 
Foreign Ministry, says: "The Federal Government is worried 
about these reports." 

