<H3> <TI>   Uranium Industry: `Not Controlled by Anybody' </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Uranium Industry: `Not Controlled by Anybody' </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0404104894 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 0949 GMT 4 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD0404104894 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Galina Nekrasova] </F>
  [Text] Lvov April 4 TASS -- The situation in the uranium 
industry is not controlled by anybody, said Konstantin Rudya, 
head of the national department for nuclear and radiation safety 
at the Ministry for Environmental Protection, after the end of 
his inspection trip to a number of uranium producing enterprises 
in Zheltiy Vodiy, Dnepropetrovsk region. He stressed that the 
extraction and processing of uranium were control-free in the 
region. Sanitary control authorities are not given the needed 
information, and there is no normative base in that sphere. 

</TEXT>

